CatDescriptText: Miss Rachael Wilson, secretary and office manager, Charles C. Wilson Insurance Agency, 2173 Wylie Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1959, pg. A1 with question: Do you believe the state and city FEPC laws are helping Negroes to get jobs they never held before?" answer reads: "Personally, I don't know. I have gotten several jobs where Negroes had never been hired before, without the help of the state or city FEPC."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Rachael Wilson wearing daisy shaped earrings and daisy patterned short sleeve dress with dark trim, standing with hands clasped interior of the Charles C. Wilson Insurance Agency
